{"search_data": "HaryanaHaryana Mukhyamantri Parivar Samridhi Yojana Apply Online Form 2020 Haryana govt. starts Mukhyamantri Parivar Samridhi Yojana apply online process, fill application / registration form to get Rs. 500 per month or Rs. 6,000 p.a as social security amount for life insurance, accidental insurance & pension benefits \u0939\u093f\u0902\u0926\u0940 \u092e\u0947\u0902 \u092a\u0922\u093c\u0947\u0902Haryana Mukhyamantri Parivar Samridhi Yojana Registration FormBelow are the important features and highlights of Mukhyamantri Parivar Samridhi Yojana:-Apply Online Link \u2013 cm-psy.haryana.gov.inEach family to get Rs. 6,000 per annum i.e Rs. 500 per month as social security amount to be utilized for payment of the beneficiary share of the centrally sponsored schemes for Pension and Insurance.Eligibility Criteria \u2013 All families whose annual income of family from all sources does not exceed Rs. 1,80,000. Or the total landholding of a family is less than 2 hectares (5 acres) . Or small businessmen with an annual turnover up to 1.5 Cr are eligible.Life Insurance Benefits (PM Jeevan Jyoti Bima Yojana \u2013 PMJJBY) \u2013 From the received Rs. 500 as social security, a premium of Rs. 330 per annum would be paid on account of Life insurance of at-least 1 family member under PMJJBY. The coverage provided is for an amount of Rs. 2 lakh in case of death of beneficiary.Accidental Insurance Benefits (PM Suraksha Bima Yojana \u2013 PMSBY) \u2013 Moreover, an amount of Rs. 12 would be paid on account of Accidental insurance of at-least 1 family member under PM Suraksha Bima Yojana. Each beneficiary to get Rs. 2 lakh life insurance cover under this PMSBY scheme.Pensionary Benefits (PM Shram Yogi Mandhan Yojana \u2013 PMSYM) \u2013 A contribution amount of Rs. 55 to 200 per month would be paid automatically from bank account as premium for PM-SYM. This premium amount is to provide pension to beneficiary under PM Shram Yogi Maandhan Yojana. On attaining the age of 60 years, pension would be provided at a rate of Rs. 3,000 per month.PM Kisan Maandhan Yojana Benefits (PMKMY) \u2013 Under this scheme, each farmer will get pension of Rs. 3,000 per month on attaining the age of 60 years.Pradhan Mantri Laghu Vyapaari Mandhan Yojna (PMLVMY) \u2013 Under this scheme, each one of the retail traders, small shopkeepers, shop owners and self employed persons will get pension of Rs. 3,000 per month on attaining the age of 60 years.PM Fasal Bima Yojana (PMFBY)Registration Form \u2013 After the launch of this scheme on 27 January 2020, the state govt. is inviting registration forms through online mode.Furthermore, the balance amount after fulfillment of all social security options would be invested in a special Systematic Investment Plan (SIP).Haryana Fights Novel Coronavirus (COVID-19) \u2013 MPSY AssistanceHaryana government led by CM Manohar Lal Khattar is providing financial assistance of Rs. 4,000 per family under the Mukhyamantri Parivar Samriddhi Yojana. Around 12,56,000 families registered under the MPSY scheme are the beneficiaries of this financial assistance. The nation-wide is ongoing and central and state govt. of Haryana are ensuring that there is no financial crisis for the poor people.Haryana CM Parivar Samridhi Yojana COVID-19The state govt. has already sent Rs. 211.62 crore assistance in the bank accounts of more than 6 lakh families registered under MPSY scheme.  Sarkari Yojana App - Download Now Source / Reference Link: https://www.aninews.in/news/national/general-news/haryana-govt-to-roll-out-mukhya-mantri-parivar-samridhi-yojana-from-aug-2120190810085045/  at  "}